    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of October 20 chart listing statistics for subway lines serving Shea and Yankee stadiums</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A chart yesterday listing statistics about subway lines serving Shea and Yankee stadiums misstated the figures for the average miles between mechanical failures for trains on the No. 7 and No. 4 lines for the last six months of 1999, as calculated by the Straphangers Campaign, a rider advocacy group. No. 7 trains traveled 125,682 miles (not 125,612), and No. 4 trains traveled 163,227 miles (not 63,227).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A chart yesterday listing statistics about subway lines serving Shea and Yankee stadiums misstated the figures for the average miles between mechanical failures for trains on the No. 7 and No. 4 lines for the last six months of 1999, as calculated by the Straphangers Campaign, a rider advocacy group. No. 7 trains traveled 125,682 miles (not 125,612), and No. 4 trains traveled 163,227 miles (not 63,227).</p>
